  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislations:\n- United States Bank Secrecy Act\n- European Union Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- UK Proceeds of Crime Act\n- Various national anti-money laundering (AML) regulations\n\n3. Key Components:\n- Customer due diligence requirements\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Financial institution compliance obligations\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms:\n- Criminal prosecutions\n- Financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Regulatory Bodies:\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Central banks\n- Financial regulators\n- Law enforcement agencies\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities by establishing comprehensive legal and regulatory standards.",
